narratelm — third-party attributions
=====================================

This project bundles reference voice audio derived from third-party
datasets. Attributions required by those datasets' licenses are recorded
below. See src/narratelm/data/voices/voices.json for the per-voice manifest.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LibriTTS-R
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Bundled voices:
  - en-ashwath-ganesan.wav  (from LibriVox reader "Ashwath Ganesan")
  - en-mark-welch.wav       (from LibriVox reader "Mark Welch")
  - en-val-grimm.wav        (from LibriVox reader "Val Grimm")

Title:    LibriTTS-R: A Restored Multi-Speaker Text-to-Speech Corpus
Authors:  Yuma Koizumi, Heiga Zen, Shigeki Karita, Yifan Ding, Kohei Yatabe,
          Nobuyuki Morioka, Michiel Bacchiani, Yu Zhang, Wei Han, Ankur Bapna
          (Google). Interspeech 2023. arXiv:2305.18802.
          LibriTTS-R is a sound-quality-restored derivative of LibriTTS
          (OpenSLR SLR60), itself derived from public-domain LibriVox
          audiobook recordings and Project Gutenberg texts.
Source:   OpenSLR SLR141 — https://www.openslr.org/141/
License:  Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
          https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Modifications: Each bundled voice is a single ~30 s, mono, 24 kHz WAV clip
excerpted from the corresponding LibriTTS-R utterance(s) and renamed to the
en-<name> convention used by this project. No other processing was applied to
the audio content. These changes are indicated as required by CC BY 4.0 §3(a).

The LibriTTS-R authors do not endorse this project or its use of the material.
